// Package basic is the ECMA-55 Minimal BASIC interpreter core: lexer, parser,
// program store, and evaluator. The intended design reaches no low-level I/O —
// all program output (and, later, input) flows through an injected
// pkg/basic/io.ConsoleOut, so the same engine drives a CLI, a conformance-test
// buffer, or a wasm host unchanged.
//
// M0 skeleton: Run emits a banner. M1 grows it into the real non-interactive
// program runner.
package "pkg/basic"

// Run drives the interpreter. (M0: emits a banner; M1: lexes/parses/runs a
// stored program.)
//
// TEMP: Run takes no injected sink and emits via the static pkg/host.WriteOut,
// because the injected-io.ConsoleOut path currently miscompiles (the
// iface-vtable 2-word-slice-arg drop, plus a VM nil-vtable bug on injected @func
// writers — see explorations/claude-todo.md and pkg/basic/io). The core's
// dependency on pkg/host is itself temporary: once injection works, this becomes
// `Run(out @io.ConsoleOut)` and the core no longer imports pkg/host.
func Run()
